bourgeoisie /ˌbʊəʒwɑːˈziː/

1. N-SING-COLL In Marxist theory, the bourgeoisie are the middle-class people who own most of the wealth in a capitalist system. (马克思主义理论中的)资产阶级 [技术] ['the' N]  →  see also petit bourgeoisie 

例： ...the suppression of the proletariat by the bourgeoisie. ...资产阶级对无产阶级的压迫。

